
###### config documentation



##### must do-s on new systems

[setup keys]

$: git clone git@github.com:N3utra1/.dotfiles.git
$: config config --local status.showUntrackedFiles 
this is so .dotfiles (git repo) behave as expected


##### documentation



#### config file (.dotfiles repo) setup

$: git init --bare $HOME/dotfiles 
$: alias config='/usr/bin/git --git-dir=$HOME/dotfiles/ --work-tree=$HOME' (add this alias to .bashrc) 
relaod bash
$: config config --local status.showUntrackedFiles no 

Basic usage example: config add /path/to/file config commit -m "A short message" config push
